snippet.textDisplay: “21 Years” is a song I wrote about the recent passing of my firstborn son, Truett Foster McKeehan. I loved him with all my heart. Until something in life hits you this hard, you never know how you will handle it. I am thankful that I have been surrounded by love, starting with God’s and extending to community near and far that have walked with us and carried us every day. Writing this song felt like an honest confession of the questions, pain, anger, doubt, mercy and promise that describes the journey I’m probably only beginning. The rest is yet to come. One thing I know is that I am not alone. God didn’t promise us a life of no pain or even tragic death, but He did promise He would never leave us or forsake us. And I’m holding dearly to that promise for my son as well as myself.

snippet.textDisplay:
I know this so very well.  We lost our 28 year old son in 2013.  There is no pain, none, like losing a child.  The second day I felt like I'd been hit by a truck; it was physical pain too.  I miss him like I cannot explain however I KNOW where he is, with our Lord and Savior helping to make a place for us, when our time comes, for our permanent home together.
When our kids were little I remember thinking "God knows how much I love my kids, He'd never take them away from me".  Growing up I had known families who had lost children.  I could not understand it and I still don't, really.  What I do understand is that our God really does have a plan for us.  He has a plan for our children... for all of us.  We have to TRUST Him.
So I say to all the parents who have lost a child, because it was said to me by a parent who'd lost a child, welcome to the club no one wants to be in but connects us forever.  No one knows what we've been through and I am thankful they don't.  Without Gods miraculous comfort and peace I do not know what my life would be like.  He is good and He KNOWs our pain.  Gods blessings to you :)  And yes, Thank you Lord for my beautiful son.  I am so blessed God chose me to be his mother.

snippet.textDisplay: I have the greatest respect for you, my friend. I'm sure that was a song that you never wanted to write. I've thought many times how I would handle losing one of my children. We will have the answer to "Why" these things happen when we bow before the King. I wrote a song for my dad when he passed in 2018 reflecting the final hours of his life. It became an integral part of my healing process. I pray that "21 Years" is the same for you. I just finished producing a song in my home studio titled "It's Only A Season". I would be honored to share it with you, if you are interested. May God Bless you and heal you through this. My prayers are with you, my friend. AJ

I cant imagine the pain that your dealing with right now Mr. Mac, and ohhh the strength it took to complete this song and video. I pray for peace, understanding, and strength for you and your family. Bless you.

snippet.textDisplay:
"Did he see you from a long way off, running to him with a father's heart, did you wrap him up inside your arms and let him know that he's home?"

Those lyrics make me imagine a scenario in my head where his son is walking through a tunnel of light and he can see the silver city from a far glistening and so beautiful, then a being of bright white light approaches him and reveals himself to be Jesus and hugs him, his son has a tear streaming down his face, but a tear of joy because he knew he made it home. Jesus wraps his arm around his shoulder and they walk off into the light toward the green meadows.

I lost my best friend on Dec 27-2019, feast of st. john. I thought nothing bad can happen on my feast. But He took my best of the best friend on that day. I keep asking God ... why why why??? I'm in the stage of PhD thesis submission and I was so busy to call him up and say Hi!!! we never had a proper goodbye. I love him so much... I asked him to visit my dream at least !!! he did :) he came to my room and sat beside my bed and he promised me that I will come back as my son and he wants to be a researcher in biochemistry... then he faded away !!!
Lord, I love you and I trust in you. St John pray for us.

snippet.textDisplay: I feel really small, saying this with all the comments, already. But, I lost my first born son, my heart. My life, the very reason im here today to even comment. My baby boy was my best friend, my teacher my light. The only person that rose above him was God. I hated God, for a moment. I was so angry with him for taking my heart right out of my chest... But then, I realized, God didn't TAKE him, he merely welcomed him home, with open arms. To hold him, until I could again. I miss my son so much. So much, that even though I love God, my FATHER, my Saviour... Im angry with him and struggle so badly with the question of why me... why MY son. God knew my life before I was given it... He knew all the death and devastation our family would endure... I'm so bitter... what did I do to deserve this wrath... I stand vigilant with my Lord, but, I'm also angry that my baby is gone...
